  "name": "asteroid-scheduler",
  "softwareLabel": "asteroid-scheduler",
  "description": "Phase-gap-aware multi-site observing window scheduler for asteroid rotational lightcurve campaigns. Given a known or candidate rotation period, identifies when and where uncovered phase intervals (gaps) are observable across any set of ground-based sites. Queries live ephemerides from the Minor Planet Center via astroquery, computes per-night dark windows using dynamically calculated astronomical twilight, evaluates lunar sky brightness via the Krisciunas-Schaefer (1991) physical model, and applies barycentric time correction with light travel time per Eastman et al. (2010). Runs without lightcurve parameters as a general multi-site visibility calculator. Output includes console display, CSV tables, and optional iCalendar export.",
